Relax and recharge in our large, two door, Ginger Peach suite.
Even when you're inside of your suite, you're connected.
Beds are topped with handcrafted artisan Ecuadorian blankets for a warm and restful night's sleep.
Enjoy a fun getaway with friends or family at our Ginger Peach suite.
Guests have access to an indoor restroom and shower while Suite Tea concierge is on site from 8-10am and 4-8pm each day.
The Ginger Peach suite features 4 luxuriously comfortable full size memory foam beds topped with handcrafted artisan Ecuadorian blankets that give the suite its own individual style.

Each suite is equipped with its own privacy tent with a camping style toilet. Porta-johns are also available to use around the clock, as needed. Additionally, there are two indoor restrooms that can be used when Suite Tea concierge is on site.
Just outside there is a picnic table and an inviting fire pit where you can eat alfresco style under the stars and roast marshmallows into the night with friends.

本客棧全面採用軟水系統，所以水龍頭、洗澡水會滑滑的，是正常現象，不是您没洗乾淨喔！

【軟水的好處】
1.柔軟衣物，清洗更徹底，洗衣柔軟，使衣物持久如新 
2.消除水垢，延長用水電器使用壽命、水管龍頭，花灑沒有水垢，出水順暢 
3.節能安全，提高熱水器效率，有效節省能源，有效消除水垢帶來的安全隱憂 
4.呵護肌膚，軟水更易被肌膚吸收，保持肌膚水分，使軟水洗車肌膚細膩有光澤 
5.潔淨安心，軟水清洗蔬果去除農藥更徹底，沖洗器具不易發黃生垢產生異味

Here it is folks, your perfect Adirondack get away. Sitting just feet from the babbling brook, our "glamping garage" and tee pee tent are a comfortable and affordable way to experience this beautiful area. We add absolutely NO EXTRA FEES!

Queen size, screened in bed with two Adirondack chairs and an Amish hickory rocker. The space has ample lighting and twinkling led lights around the inside of the tent. Feel like you are inside, while hearing the relaxing sounds of running water.
The comfortable Adirondack chairs and table, that are in the glamping garage.
LED twinkling lights surround the glamping garage.
Amish, hickory rocker in the glamping garage.
The tapestries will give you the feeling of sleeping under a star lit, Adirondack sky.
The tapestries that are behind and over the queen sized bed.
The inside, looking out of the glamping garage.

Sit around the 6' firepit. We have even added a new wood rack and sell dry campfire wood for $5 a square. We provide free paper and kindling wood to make it easy for you to start a fire. You provide the fixin's for s'mores!
Imagine sitting next to the relaxing waters, as you read a book, have a cold drink or take that afternoon nap.
The colorful tapestry that is over the queen sized bed, with LED lights on top.
This site is right on the babbling brook. Fall to sleep to the sounds of nature and running water.
Our site is good for up to four people, two in the glamping garage and two in the tee pee tent.
We have a large, tee pee tent that you are also allowed to use. It says it's for four people but would be better for two, with extra room. The thing is eight foot tall in the center!
Your view, from the site of the creek.
We have added faux sheepskins to the backs of the comfortable Adirondack chairs, to give them that warm, cozy feel.

The inside of the new shower tent. Fill the bag with hot water from the outside faucet or warm the water in the sun, at your site. Either way, you can enjoy a relaxing, private, hot shower, after those long days of hiking or sightseeing.
Seriously, what kid, of ANY age, wouldn't love the experience of sleeping in the tee pee style tent?
Even on the hottest days, it stay nice and cool under the big maple trees and by the cool waters of the babbling brook.

The dining table with the tall slot window.

The cabinets are hickory with poured in place concrete countertops. The tiled backsplash is a unique hexagonal tile which are small enough to make the curve of the wall. The floating kitchen shelves are also rough sawn white oak.
Picture window with a custom bench seat looking North.
The bathroom has a stained concrete floor with radiant heat for the winter months.

The vanity mirror is a custom frame made from barn wood which was salvaged from a barn in Iowa. The mirror rolls down the metal track to allow ample storage. The wall is a double wall in this location to allow plumbing on an exterior wall.

This is a completely custom spiral staircase crafted with locally sourced materials. The welding was done by a friend of mine. The wood treads are rough sawn white oak. The handrail is 3/16” layers of walnut laminated together.

The walnut wood in the space was from a tree which was dead on the property. We harvested the tree and cut it into boards, air dried them for a year and used the wood throughout the space. The wood beam is the most apparent feature for the walnut.

There are 3 skylights in the space which utilized the existing grain doors.

The lighting includes cove lighting at the top, sconce lights on the walls and recessed lights throughout. Along with the modern chandelier next to the mezzanine.

Det 50 m2 stora altandäcket är byggt av träd från tomten och har sol på sig från 12-19. Sköna solmadrasser finns att låna i tältet.

Tältet är minimalistiskt inrett med en futonsäng tillsammans med en skön madrass. I tältet finns el, belysning, badlakan och vattenkokare. Skulle det regna om kvällen finns det plats att flytta in det lilla bordet som står på altanen.
Sängen är bäddad med sängkläder av linnemix när ni anländer.
Från sängen ser ni det blåa havet.
Precis invid strandkanten finns en dold uteplats med ett litet bord och två stolar. Här ståendes tillsammans med en flaska Pet Nat för att fånga kvällssolen en junikväll klockan 19.
Den senaste kvällssolen fångas på de gamla vågskydden av sten byggda av fiskarna någon gång för länge sen. I bakgrunden skymtar Lausviken.
Den lugna viken på kvällstid med Lau/När till vänster och Svaje fiskeläger till höger.
Den lilla terassen gömd i en strandbuske. Här grillas det på kvällen och dukas upp frukost på morgonen. I bakgrunden syns lanternor från Ljugarns hamn.
Den lilla strandvägen som slutar precis vid tomtgränsen. I ryggen finns en mysig vandringsled längst med vattnet som tar en till Ljugarns hamn.
Från stranden snirklar sig den lilla upplysta stigen fram till tältet.
Havsutsikten från stigen. I ryggen har du tältet.
Tältet med stigen och havet i ryggen.
Utsikt mot stugan och utedass. På bilden syns grill och bord som kan flyttas efter behag.
Den lilla faluröda stugan till vänster och det gröna utedasset med tillhörande vedbod och förråd till höger.
Den enkla uteduschen som värms upp av luften och solen. Vattnet blir inte jättevarmt, men lite behagligare än brunnskallt :)
Grind vid tomtgräns med havet i bakgrunden.
Vandringsled mot Ljugarns hamn som skymtas i bakgrunden. Tar ca. 10-12 min att gå.
Två eller tre cyklar finns att låna under vistelsen beroende på antal gäster.

Welcome to Murakami! Relax in a spacious traditional Japanese tatami room! This will be your private room during your stay :)
We have an entire building devoted to hosting our guests. You will be sharing the facilities in our guesthouse with 5 other rooms.

This rate does not include any meals, but you can upgrade to the Funamori plan for an additional 6500 yen per person. If you do, a Japanese breakfast and a luxurious seafood course (Funamori) will be included! See our listing page for details.
Your host, Mr. Murakami will take you on a 1 hour boat tour around the coast to show you his beautiful hometown. You will not be able to fish from the boat, but you can enjoy the spectacular view.
Mr. Murakami can take you on a boat tour around the bay!
Mr. Murakami can take you out fishing on a dock. (You cannot fish off the boat, though).
There is a stunning beach within 5 minutes walking distance from Murakami where you can go swimming!
This is your host, Mr & Mrs Murakami. They will take great care of you during your stay :)
If you upgrade to our Funamori plan, your dinner will consist of fresh seafood caught on the same day by local fishermen, if not your host himself.
Depending on the season, you may be able to try out all kinds of seafood.
There are multiple bathrooms located in different parts the building.
You can also use the washing machine to wash your clothes.
All of our toilets are modern and clean.
We provide basic amenities such as toothbrushes, hand soap, and hair dryer in each bathroom.
When it's the men's turn, you will see the blue banner.
When this red banner is hung up, the bath is only available for women.
This is the changing area where you can put your clothes.
In Japan, it is customary to wash your body first by the showers and then enter the hot bath once you are clean.
The dining area is in a separate building. Both dinner and breakfast will take place here.
There are also a few sinks in the changing area.
There is a common area in the guesthouse, where you can talk with other guests and enjoy a game of Go.
We provide air conditioners in each room with both heating and cooling functions.
Here are some guests enjoying fishing off of the dock!
Here are some guests who stayed with us enjoying the boat tour!
Two vending machines are located at the entrance of the guesthouse where you can easily get soft drinks and alcoholic beverages.
This is the view of the Fishermen's village from the sea.
As long as the weather permits, you will be able to enjoy 1 hour at sea with your host, Mr. Murakami.
If you walk 5 minutes along the coast, you will be able to reach a lovely beach area where you can bathe in the ocean.
The water is spotless and barely any people are here, so you are likely to have the whole beach to yourself ;)
There is free parking for all guests staying at Murakami.
Locals collect seaweed and hang them under the sun to get dried seaweed.
When you have time, a stroll around the village will give you great insight on how the villagers here live. Their lifestyle has remained mostly unchanged for hundreds of years.
He will show you all the fishing spots around the bay. You cannot fish from the boat, but you can do dock and pier fishing.
Please feel free to drop us a message if you want to find out more about staying at Murakami. You are welcome any time!

The Spirit of the Wild is an eco-chic and woodsy, Bohème luxury Belle Tent curated and offered to lovers and friends, wanderers and explorers. For lovers 1 Queen bed,  friends 1 Queen and 2 Twin, for the Wolf Pack up to 4 in their own Twin beds.

We can’t wait to use our spirited style to create a bespoke outdoor dining experience for you. From eco-chic and woodsy, to native wildflower gardens to pastel sandy beach style, let the Spirit of the Wilderness show you the raw beauty of the wild.

Splitting wood in the fresh air has never been so satisfying. Swing the weighted head with ease as its wide angle, carbon steel split blade keeps its edge time after time. Swing our signature axe or, let us do the splitting ($12.50 a bundle).

Perfect for hearty recipes make this a camp chef’s essential. You can rely on the briquette heating guide on the bottom side of the lid to master every roast and cobbler or request campfire catering from our spirited camp fire chefs. (Prices Vary)

Campfire Catering is a return to the origins of cooking and hospitality.  A celebration of the spirit of our name in which we gather around a fire, create honest food, and share it with friends.  We hope you decide to add it to your wild experience.

Partake in 1927 S'mores' artisanal, mouth-watering version of a classic American treat. Grahams and marshmallows are handcrafted from scratch using ingredients from local purveyors. S'mores for four ($20). Guests can use Spirit of the Wild Skewers.

A reversible cast iron griddle perfect for camp cooking. Use flat side for eggs, crab cakes, and fajitas, then flip to the grill side for burgers, kebabs, and vegetables. Naturally nonstick cast iron heats evenly, so your food is perfect every time.

Hole in the Wall, rocky beaches, giant drift logs, pounding waves and views of offshore islands known as 'seastacks' characterize Rialto Beach. Accessible by Mora Road, off of LaPush Road. Rent vintage beach bikes and ride the short 3 mile distance.

Craft Cocktail Kits Available -  As the sun begins to sit, little embers of celebration scatter across your campfire. BYOB and we’ll pair our Craft Cocktail Kits ($12) with the freshest and best cocktails ingredients from our gardens to your glass!
Foraging for wild foods can take some work, but it is worthwhile. Learn about the plants and animals you can find - and what to avoid. Look at Call of the Wild Experiences on Airbnb.

The Misc. Goods Co. playing cards are a perfect match for Spirit of the Wild’s guests. These cards show a new perspective on the classic style of a card game while weaving in new ideas, references and back story - perfect for the Wild Ones!
Roll the Dice! The Spirit of the Wild’s Giant Wooden Yard Dice Outdoor Lawn Game will bring wild fun to any outdoor dice game you have during your stay.
